    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing 141 species in two families including anis, roadrunners, and the hoatzin, with one species extinct since 1600. They are long-tailed birds with rearward or sideward facing toes, feeding on both fruits and small animals, most are arboreal but a few are terrestrial, and some are brood parasites.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
